Sentencas: Electrospun La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF) nanorod cathodes are investigated.
Titulo: Electrochemical Impedance Spectroscopy of Electrospun La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ Nanorod Cathodes for Intermediate Temperature - Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Morphological characterization shows that the nanorods are arranged into a 3-D stochastic structure, with multiple contact points with each other.
Titulo: Electrochemical Impedance Spectroscopy of Electrospun La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ Nanorod Cathodes for Intermediate Temperature - Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Experimental characterization of symmetrical button cells through electrochemical impedance spectroscopy demonstrates an electrode polarization resistance R-p = 3.9 omega cm(2) at 940 K and R-p = 10.9 omega cm(2) at 890 K.
Titulo: Electrochemical Impedance Spectroscopy of Electrospun La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ Nanorod Cathodes for Intermediate Temperature - Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The impedance results, measured from 890 K up to 1,200 K, show that the depressed Gerischer behavior is not an intrinsic feature of the electrode, since it appears only at certain well defined temperatures, and then it tends to disappear for other operating temperatures.
Titulo: Electrochemical Impedance Spectroscopy of Electrospun La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ Nanorod Cathodes for Intermediate Temperature - Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Equivalent circuit model fitting is accomplished through the depressed Gerischer element, and also through an alternative circuit based on a normal Gerischer coupled to an RQ element.
Titulo: Electrochemical Impedance Spectroscopy of Electrospun La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ Nanorod Cathodes for Intermediate Temperature - Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The superior fitting capability of the latter equivalent circuit is demonstrated.
Titulo: Electrochemical Impedance Spectroscopy of Electrospun La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ Nanorod Cathodes for Intermediate Temperature - Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The latter circuit allows to assess separately the impedance contribution of the electrode bulk, associated to the Gerischer element, and of the electrode/electrolyte interface, associated to the RQ element.
Titulo: Electrochemical Impedance Spectroscopy of Electrospun La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ Nanorod Cathodes for Intermediate Temperature - Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Both the related polarization resistances are larger with the electrospun LSCF 3-D random nanorod electrode, rather than with an electrospun LSCF electrode with unbroken nanofibers laying neatly in-plane over the electrolyte.
Titulo: Electrochemical Impedance Spectroscopy of Electrospun La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ Nanorod Cathodes for Intermediate Temperature - Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
